Burt Reynolds' personal memorabilia, including the infamous Smokey and the Bandit Trans Am car, fetched more than $2.5 million at a Las Vegas auction. 

More than 600 items, including his 1998 Golden Globe for Boogie Nights and the canoe made for his movie Deliverance were up for sale. 

The 78-year-old star strongly denied speculation that he was selling the collection because he was bankrupt saying before the sale, 'I want everyone to know that contrary to what all the news outlets are saying, I am not broke.' 

Instead he said his house has become a shrine to himself.  

