The home was listed for sale at $15 million in 2006 and the bank sued the actor in 2011 when he fell behind on mortgage payments, claiming he hadn't made one since September, 2010.

Among the items for sale was the stagecoach that he and now ex-wife Loni Anderson rode in after their wedding on the Florida estate in 1998.

The auction at The Palms in Las Vegas also included a pair of cowboy boots he wore in the hit 1996 movie, Striptease, co-starring Demi Moore.

